AU  - Schivardi, Fabiano
T1  - Employment and Wage Insurance within Firms: Worldwide Evidence
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx104
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 31
IS  - 4
SP  - 1298
EP  - 1340
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using a firm-level international panel data set, we study if unemployment insurance offered by the government and by firms are substitutes. We exploit cross-country and time-series variation in public unemployment insurance as a shifter of workers’ demand for insurance within firms, and family versus nonfamily ownership as a shifter of firms’ supply of insurance. Our evidence supports the substitutability hypothesis: employment stability in family firms is greater, and the wage discount larger, in countries and periods with less generous public unemployment insurance, whereas no such substitutability emerges for nonfamily firms.Received July 18, 2015; editorial decision August 8, 2017 by Editor Francesca Cornelli.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx104
ER  - 



