TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gonzalez-Uribe, Juanita
AU  - Leatherbee, Michael
T1  - The Effects of Business Accelerators on Venture Performance: Evidence from Start-Up Chile
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx103
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 31
IS  - 4
SP  - 1566
EP  - 1603
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Do business accelerators affect new venture performance? We investigate this question in the context of Start-Up Chile, an ecosystem accelerator. We focus on two treatment conditions typically found in business accelerators: basic services of funding and coworking space, and additional entrepreneurship schooling. Using a regression discontinuity design, we show that schooling bundled with basic services can significantly increase new venture performance. In contrast, we find no evidence that basic services affect performance on their own. Our results are most relevant for ecosystem accelerators that attract young and early-stage businesses and suggest that entrepreneurial capital matters in new ventures.Received September 1, 2015; editorial decision July 30, 2017 by Editor Francesca Cornelli.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx103
ER  - 



